						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Zimbabwe-Researchers-developing-new-ways-to-purify-water" title="Zimbabwe: Researchers developing new ways to purify water" alt="link">Zimbabwe: Researchers developing new ways to purify water</a></h2>

	
					<p>








 




  
  

	
	<a href="/var/knowledge/storage/images/media/images/nust/252476-1-eng-GB/NUST.png" rel="lightbox[]" >	
	  </a>
	
		
			
	
  	






	 
  





	Scientists at Bulawayo's National University of Science and Technology (NUST) have embarked on research to develop simple and affordable water purification methods, as more than a billion people live without safe drinking water in developing countries. Water and sanitation experts are currently investigating if a powder made from the seeds of the Moringa Oleifera, commonly known as the drumstick or horseradish tree, can be used as a filter to purify water. (Source: IPS, 25 March 2009)</p>
							<p><span class="date">17/04/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Zimbabwe-Researchers-developing-new-ways-to-purify-water">Read more...</a>
</div>
